        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize the logging subsystem. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Sets up the log storage buffer and configures timestamp and filtering.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">log_buf</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Ring buffer for storing log entries. Should be initialized with overwrite mode enabled. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">timestamp_fn</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Function to get current timestamp in milliseconds (e.g., HAL_GetTick). Can be NULL if timestamps are not needed. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">min_level</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Minimum log level to record. Logs below this level are silently discarded. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
